<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1735" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1735">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11D29/70.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 28, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your September 19. The Department has no objection to the reexamination
                            of such witnesses as may be readily available but could not consent to
                            the presentation of witnesses who have left Panama.</p>
                        <p>Continue to urge upon the Government of Panama the necessity of bringing
                            the investigation to an early conclusion.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>